import Mathlib
open TopologicalSpace Filter
open scoped Topology

/-- Let U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ be a domain and f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ be holomorphic. Translate to Lean4: show f is analytic on U (i.e., analytic on the set U).
We use the hypothesis that f is differentiable on U (DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) and U is open. -/
theorem holomorphic_on_analytic {H : Type} [TopologicalSpace H] (f : H ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ) (U : Set H) (hopen : IsOpen U)
  (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) : AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U := by sorry

import Mathlib
open TopologicalSpace Filter
open scoped Topology

/-- If U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ is open and f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ is differentiable on U, then f is analytic on U. -/
theorem holomorphic_on_analytic (f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ) (U : Set ‚ÑÇ) (hopen : IsOpen U)
  (h : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) : AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f U := by sorry
